  "text": "Since McGeer introduced the concept of passive dynamic walking [CITATION_1] , a number of energy-efficient and naturally walking machines have been built. However, the stability and robustness of this kind of biped robots are still not satisfactory. This is due to the inherent properties of dynamic walking, which exploits the natural limit cycle of the kinematic structure, as opposed to trajectory-based humanoid robots (such as the Asimo robot by Honda).",
